external_knowledge:
- "wells" metaphorically refers to "pump installations";
- "water team" refers to all pump installations collectively;
- "efficiency of the water team" refers to the overall average efficiency of all motors across all pump installations;
- "dragging the efficiency... below the team average" means the average efficiency of the motors associated with particular pump installations is less than the overall average efficiency.

The term "typical voltage levels" refers to the average voltage; "cleaning maintenance" indicates maintenance descriptions containing the word 'clean'.;
[SOLAR ARRAYS] refers to unique solar energy setups identified by `solar_array_id`.;
[MOTOR_VOLTAGE] is related to the operational voltage levels of the motors associated with these arrays.;
[Maintenance Logs] contain records of performed maintenance, including descriptions.;
[Voltage] is a measurement of electric potential, critical for assessing the operational status of motors.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT pump_id
FROM motor_performance
WHERE efficiency < (SELECT AVG(efficiency) FROM motor_performance);

SELECT COUNT(pump_id) 
FROM pumps 
WHERE strftime('%s', 'now') > strftime('%s', last_maintenance_date);

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM pumps 
WHERE power_rating > (SELECT AVG(power_rating) FROM pumps);

SELECT location, COUNT(pump_id) as pump_count
FROM pumps
GROUP BY location;

SELECT SUM(wattage)
FROM solar_arrays
WHERE pump_id = 1;

SELECT DISTINCT T2.name
FROM maintenance_logs AS T1
JOIN technicians AS T2 ON T1.technician_id = T2.technician_id;

SELECT AVG(watts) 
FROM motor_performance 
WHERE pump_id IN (SELECT pump_id FROM pumps WHERE location = 'Farm 1');

external_knowledge:
- 'less efficient' refers to motor efficiency less than 50%; 
- 'recently' means more than two years ago, specifically after 2022-01-01; 
- 'frequent issues' implies more than five alerts.

sql:
SELECT p.name, p.location, p.last_maintenance_date
FROM pumps p
WHERE (julianday('now') - julianday(p.last_maintenance_date)) > 30;

SELECT p.name AS PumpName, s.wattage AS SolarArrayWatts
FROM pumps p
LEFT JOIN solar_arrays s ON p.pump_id = s.pump_id;

SELECT DISTINCT t.name, t.email
FROM maintenance_logs ml
JOIN technicians t ON ml.technician_id = t.technician_id;

